The paper proposes a new approach to recommending method names, which is a software engineering task. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed approach uses graph embedding techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions programming languages and limitations on applicable situations, suggesting cs.PL (Programming Languages) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the evaluation experiment involves measuring the effectiveness of the proposed technique, which could be considered a performance evaluation, suggesting cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category.
